Privacy Policy
Effective Date: [2024]

Conscious Factory operates the YouTube Bot application (the "App"). 
This Privacy Policy outlines how we collect, use, and disclose personal information from users when using the App.

1. Information We Collect
We collect the following types of information:

YouTube Data: With your explicit consent, we may collect data from your YouTube account, such as channel information, video details, and analytics. This data is collected through the use of the YouTube API and is subject to YouTube’s Terms of Service and Google Privacy Policy.
Personal Information: We collect your email address or other identifiable information during account setup or app usage.
Usage Data: We may collect information on how you interact with the App, including logs and diagnostic data to help improve performance.
2. How We Use Your Information
We use the information collected to:

Provide, operate, and maintain the App.
Personalize and enhance your experience.
Communicate with you regarding updates or support for the App.
Analyze and improve the App’s functionality.
3. Sharing Your Information
We do not share or sell your personal information with third parties, except:

When required by law or legal processes.
With your consent, such as in cases of third-party integration.
To protect our rights, property, or safety.
4. Data Retention
We retain your information for as long as necessary to fulfill the purposes outlined in this Privacy Policy or comply with legal obligations.

5. Security
We take reasonable precautions to protect your personal information. However, no method of transmission over the internet or electronic storage is 100% secure, so we cannot guarantee its absolute security.

6. Your Rights
You have the right to:

Access the personal information we collect about you.
Request corrections or deletions of personal data.
Withdraw your consent to data processing at any time.
7. Third-Party Services
The App may contain links to third-party services (e.g., YouTube). We are not responsible for the privacy practices of these services, and you should review their privacy policies before providing any personal information.

8. Changes to This Privacy Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any changes by updating the "Effective Date" at the top of this policy.

